Class StructureLibAPI

java.lang.Object
com.gtnewhorizon.structurelib.StructureLibAPI
public class StructureLibAPI extends Object
A stable interface into the structure lib's internals. Backwards compatibility is maintained to the maximum extend possible.

  • Method Details

    • enableInstrument

      public static void enableInstrument(Object identifier)
      Start instrumenting for the current thread only. When instrumentation is enabled, IStructureDefinition's builtin iteration methods will send StructureEvent and its subclasses when appropriate. Otherwise, these events will not be sent at all, regardless of whether a listener for these events are registered.

      Identifiers are required to be value-comparable, i.e. overrides Object.equals(Object). Suggested identifier includes

      • Mod Instance or ModContainer
      • IConstructable and its friends, if you are triggering structure check via this interface.
      • ResourceLocation

      It's an API abuse for normal IStructureDefinition users to depend on this feature. They have full control and full knowledge of the IStructureDefinition they are using. Using events to instrument the structure check/autoplace is completely unnecessary and does nothing but add overhead.

      Instruments are required to call disableInstrument() whenever it is done with its business, as there can be only one instrument for any given thread.

      Parameters:
      identifier - an identifier sent along the actual event.
      Throws:
      IllegalStateException - if instrument has already been enabled.

    • disableInstrument

      public static void disableInstrument()
      Stop instrumenting.
      Throws:
      IllegalStateException - if instrumenting hasn't been enabled.

    • startHinting

      public static void startHinting(World w)
      Start a batch of hinting. All hints particles generated during one batch will be considered to belong to one hologram.

      You don't need to call this unless your constructable tool didn't call ConstructableUtility.handle(ItemStack, EntityPlayer, World, int, int, int, int)

    • endHinting

      public static void endHinting(World w)
      End current batch of hinting. All hints particles generated during one batch will be considered to belong to one hologram.

      You don't need to call this unless your constructable tool didn't call ConstructableUtility.handle(ItemStack, EntityPlayer, World, int, int, int, int)

    • hintParticleTinted

      public static void hintParticleTinted(World w, int x, int y, int z, IIcon[] icons, short[] RGBa)
      Generate a new hint particle on client side at given location using given textures with a tint.
      Parameters:
      w - World to spawn. Usually the client world.
      x - x coord
      y - y coord
      z - z coord
      icons - 6 texture. in forge direction order.
      RGBa - a 4 short array. tint in rgba form. currently alpha channel is ignored, but we might change this later on.

    • hintParticleTinted

      public static void hintParticleTinted(World w, int x, int y, int z, Block block, int meta, short[] RGBa)

      Parameters:
      w - World to spawn. Usually the client world.
      x - x coord
      y - y coord
      z - z coord
      block - block to take texture from
      meta - the meta of block to take texture from
      RGBa - a 4 short array. tint in rgba form. currently alpha channel is ignored, but we might change this later on.

    • markHintParticleError

      public static boolean markHintParticleError(EntityPlayer player, World w, int x, int y, int z)
      Update the tint of given hint particle. Do nothing if particle not found.

      Can be called on either client side or server side. Server side will schedule a network message to update it for this player only. Will do nothing if no hint particle is found at given location.

      Returns:
      false if nothing updated. true if updated or update instruction sent.

    • updateHintParticleTint

      Returns:
      false if nothing updated. true if updated.

    • queryAlignment

      public static void queryAlignment(IAlignmentProvider provider)
      Query the ExtendedFacing of this tile entity from client side. Can be sent only on client side. The ExtendedFacing will later be set onto given tile entity via IAlignment.setExtendedFacing(ExtendedFacing) upon arrival of server reply.

      The server side will query the ExtendedFacing of this provider using IAlignment.getExtendedFacing()

      Throws:
      IllegalArgumentException - if is not tile entity or provided a null alignment

    • sendAlignment

      public static void sendAlignment(IAlignmentProvider provider)
      Send the ExtendedFacing of this Tile Entity to all players. Can be called on server side only.

      The receiving tile entity will receive the ExtendedFacing via its IAlignment.setExtendedFacing(ExtendedFacing) method.

      Throws:
      IllegalArgumentException - if is not tile entity or provided a null alignment

    • sendAlignment

      public static void sendAlignment(IAlignmentProvider provider, EntityPlayerMP player)

      The receiving tile entity will receive the ExtendedFacing via its IAlignment.setExtendedFacing(ExtendedFacing) method.

      Throws:
      IllegalArgumentException - if is not tile entity or provided a null alignment

    • sendAlignment

    • addThrottledChat

      public static void addThrottledChat(Object throttleKey, EntityPlayer player, IChatComponent text, short intervalRequired)
      Send chat to player, but throttled.
      Parameters:
      throttleKey - throttle key. Must properly implement Object.hashCode() and Object.equals(Object) to handle value equality.
      player - player to send chat to
      text - chat to send
      intervalRequired - interval required before last recorded time to actually send the message. unit in millisecond. we purposefully chose to not use a bigger data type to limit how long this interval can be

    • addThrottledChat

      public static void addThrottledChat(Object throttleKey, EntityPlayer player, IChatComponent text, short intervalRequired, boolean forceUpdateLastSend)
      Send chat to player, but throttled.
      Parameters:
      throttleKey - throttle key. Must properly implement Object.hashCode() and Object.equals(Object) to handle value equality.
      player - player to send chat to
      text - chat to send
      intervalRequired - interval required before last recorded time to actually send the message. unit in millisecond. we purposefully chose to not use a bigger data type to limit how long this interval can be
      forceUpdateLastSend - if true, always update the last send time, even if the message isn't actually sent.

    • registerChannelItem

      public static void registerChannelItem(String channel, String modid, int channelValue, ItemStack stack)
      Register an item stack as an indicator for a (channel, value) pair.
      Parameters:
      channel - channel key
      modid - your modid
      channelValue - value
      stack - item stack. having a metadata of OreDictionary.WILDCARD_VALUE will match without comparing NBT or metadata value. having a tag with tag.getBoolean("*") == true will match without comparing NBT.
